      <article class="post-78872 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized" id="post-78872">
  <header class="entry-header">

          <h2 class="entry-title"><a href="https://marginalrevolution.com/marginalrevolution/2020/07/friday-assorted-links-269.html">Friday assorted links</a></h2>
    
      <div class="byline">
        by&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="author"><a href="/about">Tyler Cowen</a></span>
        <time class="entry-date published" datetime="2020-07-03 10:47:49">July 3, 2020 at 10:47 am </time>
                                          </div><!-- /.byline -->
  </header><!-- /.entry-header -->
  <div class="entry-content">
    <div class="pf-content"><p>1. <a href="https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2020-07-02/nathan-tankus-s-newsletter-subscribers-don-t-care-about-diplomas?utm_content=business&amp;utm_source=twitter&amp;utm_medium=social&amp;utm_campaign=socialflow-organic&amp;cmpid=socialflow-twitter-business&amp;sref=htOHjx5Y" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Profile of Nathan Tankus</a>.  And <a href="https://theviewer.is/a-clockwork-orange/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Clockwork Orange review</a>.</p>
<p>2. <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2006.14979" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">The growing influence of Sci-hub</a>.</p>
<p>3. <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2020/07/01/us/somerville-polyamorous-domestic-partnership.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Somerville, Mass. recognizes polyamory</a> (NYT).</p>
<p>4. <a href="https://www.theguardian.com/media/2020/jul/01/france-bans-dutch-bike-tv-ad-for-creating-climate-of-fear" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">France bans Dutch bike TV ad for creating &#8216;climate of fear&#8217; about cars</a>.  &#8220;The French advertising code prohibits the exploitation of fear and suffering in commercials.&#8221;</p>
<p>5. &#8220;&#8230;a novel song sung by white-throated sparrows is spreading across Canada at an unprecedented rate. What’s more, the new song appears to be replacing the pre-existing melody, which dates as far back as the 1960s.&#8221;  Link <a href="https://gizmodo.com/a-viral-new-bird-song-in-canada-is-causing-sparrows-t-1844245103" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">here</a>.</p>
